I'm looking at some of the prices listed here on armslist and I'm wondering if anyone is willing to pay them. Just a few ads down is a standard GI mag listed for $100. I would single feed bullets before I would pay that price. You shouldn't be willing to pay that price either. 

www.Wideners.com still has 20 round AR mags for $22 and 30 round mags for $30 (the 30 round mags are bright pink). Both of these mags have magpul followers and are in stock. 

cheaperthandirt.com has IMI 30 round mags for $30 (they are also price gouging SOBs that have pmags listed for $80) do business with them if you have to but remember what they are doing when this is all over and take your business elsewhere. As for the rest of you Dealer gouging on armslist I hope you SOBs go out of business. I understand a small markup for hard to get items but if you treat your customers like this I hope they turn their backs on you when they have the option. 

Today I went to Fin Feather and Fur in Ashland and they had windowed pmags for $40. They also had some 5.56 ammo in stock. Lake City M855 420 rounds for $250. Federal M193 20 rounds for $13. Don't pay a buck a round for 223, the prices listed on armslist are insane. Flag those listings and click the overpriced button. 

Things are coming back into stock at your local stores and your favorite online retailers so check there first. I'm not saying you shouldn't stock up, just be smart about it.

title: For Sale:  2009 SUZUKI DR 650 Dual Sport, LOW MILES, near perfect - $5995 (KNOX-MARYVILLE)
postcontent:
This is a near perfect, low miles Suzuki Dr. 650 Dual Sport. 

I bought this motor cycle with intentions of getting my license and taking sunday rides here in the beautiful mountains of east TN.

My plans changed because of health issues. It is a near perfect bike as I said, and it is ready to take across the country if you want to. 

I never did get my license, but I did ride it in my driveway for a few miles.......I bought it last year and it has been covered ever since except for a weekly start and short ride just to keep it lubricated.

It has been professionally tuned and carbed........or whatever it is everyone wants to do to make it run better and has some kind of special exhaust system to make it breath better. I have the stock pipe that goes with it. All I can say is it is silky smooth. It is electric start and starts easily every time.

By the way, this bike has the famous 650, four stroke engine labeled as "Bullet Proof".

I am using the pictures that was used when I bought it, (notice oil cooler). I hate to sell, but medical issues have come up, and I won't be riding like I had wanted to do.

You can look at the pics and tell it's a beautiful bike. I bought it, got it insured and tagged......but I never got to ride it except in my driveway.

If you are interested in a near perfect bike that looks and runs amazing.........well actually I have never had it over about 20 MPH, so I can not say how it runs on the highyway, but I can assure you it would have more power than you would ever want and will run smooth as silk I am certain.

This is an amazing bike that I looked for for about 2 years before I found it. I am in no hurry to sell this bike, I just thought I would put it up for sale early for those early bird cycle people who is looking for that special bike. It is a special bike for someone who wants to take long rides often........it was my dream bike.

Email me for more specifics if you want to get the jump on a really nice bike before the spring thaw and you don't exactly fit on the "other" bigger bikes. This one is plenty big enough. This is a special purpose bike that could take you just about anywhere in the world you ever wanted to go.

I have the battery out now to preserve it in a heated space, so I would need a day to put it in and uncover the bike just to show it.

Please, serious inquiries only, thank you.

Thanks for taking the time to read this.
